cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with deep semantic segmentation algorithms, which is a computer vision task, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also proposes a self-supervised learning model, which falls under the purview of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves designing an aggregation strategy and computing global context similarity, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) respectively. Finally, the paper involves adapting semantic segmentation models from one domain to another, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
